{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"It's often said that you can tell\na lot about a person"},{"time":3927,"text":"by looking at what's on their bookshelves."},{"time":7679,"text":"What do my bookshelves say about me?"},{"time":10402,"text":"Well, when I asked myself\nthis question a few years ago,"},{"time":14110,"text":"I made an alarming discovery."},{"time":17131,"text":"I'd always thought of myself\nas a fairly cultured,"},{"time":20159,"text":"cosmopolitan sort of person."},{"time":22608,"text":"But my bookshelves told\na rather different story."},{"time":26439,"text":"Pretty much all the titles on them"},{"time":28115,"text":"were by British or North American authors,"},{"time":30998,"text":"and there was almost\nnothing in translation."},{"time":34327,"text":"Discovering this massive,\ncultural blind spot in my reading"},{"time":38201,"text":"came as quite a shock."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40026,"text":"And when I thought about it,\nit seemed like a real shame."},{"time":43543,"text":"I knew there had to be lots\nof amazing stories out there"},{"time":46939,"text":"by writers working in languages\nother than English."},{"time":50340,"text":"And it seemed really sad to think\nthat my reading habits meant"},{"time":53666,"text":"I would probably never encounter them."},{"time":56435,"text":"So, I decided to prescribe myself"},{"time":59325,"text":"an intensive course of global reading."},{"time":62602,"text":"2012 was set to be a very\ninternational year for the UK;"},{"time":66364,"text":"it was the year of the London Olympics."},{"time":68460,"text":"And so I decided to use it\nas my time frame"},{"time":72006,"text":"to try to read a novel,\nshort story collection"},{"time":75237,"text":"or memoir from every country in the world."},{"time":80771,"text":"And so I did."},{"time":82128,"text":"And it was very exciting"},{"time":83779,"text":"and I learned some remarkable things"},{"time":85699,"text":"and made some wonderful connections"},{"time":87838,"text":"that I want to share with you today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90088,"text":"But it started with some\npractical problems."},{"time":93849,"text":"After I'd worked out which of the many\ndifferent lists of countries in the world"},{"time":98540,"text":"to use for my project,"},{"time":100770,"text":"I ended up going with the list\nof UN-recognized nations,"},{"time":103944,"text":"to which I added Taiwan,"},{"time":105191,"text":"which gave me a total of 196 countries."},{"time":109143,"text":"And after I'd worked out\nhow to fit reading and blogging"},{"time":112022,"text":"about, roughly, four books a week"},{"time":114356,"text":"around working five days a week,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":117491,"text":"I then had to face up to the fact\nthat I might even not be able"},{"time":121219,"text":"to get books in English\nfrom every country."},{"time":124546,"text":"Only around 4.5 percent\nof the literary works published"},{"time":128315,"text":"each year in the UK are translations,"},{"time":130990,"text":"and the figures are similar for much\nof the English-speaking world."},{"time":134640,"text":"Although, the proportion\nof translated books published"},{"time":137617,"text":"in many other countries is a lot higher."},{"time":141101,"text":"4.5 percent is tiny enough to start with,"},{"time":144433,"text":"but what that figure doesn't tell you"},{"time":146292,"text":"is that many of those books\nwill come from countries"},{"time":148989,"text":"with strong publishing networks"},{"time":151187,"text":"and lots of industry professionals\nprimed to go out and sell those titles"},{"time":155378,"text":"to English-language publishers."},{"time":157711,"text":"So, for example, although well over 100\nbooks are translated from French"},{"time":162307,"text":"and published in the UK each year,"},{"time":164234,"text":"most of them will come from countries\nlike France or Switzerland."},{"time":169107,"text":"French-speaking Africa, on the other hand,"},{"time":171869,"text":"will rarely ever get a look-in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174284,"text":"The upshot is that there are\nactually quite a lot of nations"},{"time":177631,"text":"that may have little or even no\ncommercially available literature"},{"time":181286,"text":"in English."},{"time":183074,"text":"Their books remain invisible to readers"},{"time":186164,"text":"of the world's most published language."},{"time":190002,"text":"But when it came to reading the world,"},{"time":191844,"text":"the biggest challenge of all for me"},{"time":193638,"text":"was that fact that I didn't\nknow where to start."},{"time":197201,"text":"Having spent my life reading\nalmost exclusively British"},{"time":200583,"text":"and North American books,"},{"time":202256,"text":"I had no idea how to go about\nsourcing and finding stories"},{"time":205869,"text":"and choosing them from much\nof the rest of the world."},{"time":208604,"text":"I couldn't tell you how to source\na story from Swaziland."},{"time":212013,"text":"I wouldn't know a good novel from Namibia."},{"time":215125,"text":"There was no hiding it --"},{"time":216742,"text":"I was a clueless literary xenophobe."},{"time":220541,"text":"So how on earth was I\ngoing to read the world?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":223777,"text":"I was going to have to ask for help."},{"time":225658,"text":"So in October 2011, I registered my blog,"},{"time":229181,"text":"ayearofreadingtheworld.com,"},{"time":230976,"text":"and I posted a short appeal online."},{"time":233863,"text":"I explained who I was,"},{"time":235116,"text":"how narrow my reading had been,"},{"time":237148,"text":"and I asked anyone who cared to"},{"time":239029,"text":"to leave a message suggesting\nwhat I might read"},{"time":241618,"text":"from other parts of the planet."},{"time":243913,"text":"Now, I had no idea whether\nanyone would be interested,"},{"time":248010,"text":"but within a few hours\nof me posting that appeal online,"},{"time":251148,"text":"people started to get in touch."},{"time":253608,"text":"At first, it was friends and colleagues."},{"time":256466,"text":"Then it was friends of friends."},{"time":258383,"text":"And pretty soon, it was strangers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261399,"text":"Four days after I put that appeal online,"},{"time":264225,"text":"I got a message from a woman\ncalled Rafidah in Kuala Lumpur."},{"time":268292,"text":"She said she loved\nthe sound of my project,"},{"time":270991,"text":"could she go to her local\nEnglish-language bookshop"},{"time":273914,"text":"and choose my Malaysian book\nand post it to me?"},{"time":277912,"text":"I accepted enthusiastically,"},{"time":279689,"text":"and a few weeks later,"},{"time":281215,"text":"a package arrived containing\nnot one, but two books --"},{"time":287263,"text":"Rafidah's choice from Malaysia,"},{"time":290908,"text":"and a book from Singapore\nthat she had also picked out for me."},{"time":296428,"text":"Now, at the time, I was amazed"},{"time":298889,"text":"that a stranger more than 6,000 miles away"},{"time":302489,"text":"would go to such lengths to help someone"},{"time":304438,"text":"she would probably never meet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307100,"text":"But Rafidah's kindness proved\nto be the pattern for that year."},{"time":311240,"text":"Time and again, people went\nout of their way to help me."},{"time":315226,"text":"Some took on research on my behalf,"},{"time":317859,"text":"and others made detours\non holidays and business trips"},{"time":320906,"text":"to go to bookshops for me."},{"time":323526,"text":"It turns out, if you want\nto read the world,"},{"time":326786,"text":"if you want to encounter it\nwith an open mind,"},{"time":330211,"text":"the world will help you."},{"time":333118,"text":"When it came to countries"},{"time":334357,"text":"with little or no commercially\navailable literature in English,"},{"time":337887,"text":"people went further still."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340689,"text":"Books often came from surprising sources."},{"time":344536,"text":"My Panamanian read, for example,\ncame through a conversation"},{"time":347599,"text":"I had with the Panama Canal on Twitter."},{"time":351497,"text":"Yes, the Panama Canal\nhas a Twitter account."},{"time":355731,"text":"And when I tweeted at it about my project,"},{"time":358129,"text":"it suggested that I might like to try\nand get hold of the work"},{"time":361532,"text":"of the Panamanian author\nJuan David Morgan."},{"time":364898,"text":"I found Morgan's website\nand I sent him a message,"},{"time":367492,"text":"asking if any of his\nSpanish-language novels"},{"time":369948,"text":"had been translated into English."},{"time":372432,"text":"And he said that nothing\nhad been published,"},{"time":374887,"text":"but he did have an unpublished translation"},{"time":377341,"text":"of his novel \"The Golden Horse.\""},{"time":379887,"text":"He emailed this to me,"},{"time":381249,"text":"allowing me to become\none of the first people ever"},{"time":384407,"text":"to read that book in English."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386929,"text":"Morgan was by no means the only wordsmith"},{"time":389603,"text":"to share his work with me in this way."},{"time":392015,"text":"From Sweden to Palau,"},{"time":393801,"text":"writers and translators\nsent me self-published books"},{"time":397816,"text":"and unpublished manuscripts of books"},{"time":399570,"text":"that hadn't been picked\nup by Anglophone publishers"},{"time":402474,"text":"or that were no longer available,"},{"time":404520,"text":"giving me privileged glimpses\nof some remarkable imaginary worlds."},{"time":410008,"text":"I read, for example,"},{"time":411183,"text":"about the Southern African king\nNgungunhane, who led the resistance"},{"time":415797,"text":"against the Portuguese\nin the 19th century;"},{"time":419113,"text":"and about marriage rituals\nin a remote village"},{"time":421908,"text":"on the shores of the Caspian sea\nin Turkmenistan."},{"time":426524,"text":"I met Kuwait's answer to Bridget Jones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430450,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":433301,"text":"And I read about an orgy\nin a tree in Angola."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440870,"text":"But perhaps the most amazing example"},{"time":443046,"text":"of the lengths that people\nwere prepared to go to"},{"time":445474,"text":"to help me read the world,"},{"time":447125,"text":"came towards the end of my quest,"},{"time":449598,"text":"when I tried to get hold of a book\nfrom the tiny, Portuguese-speaking"},{"time":453456,"text":"African island nation\nof São Tomé and Príncipe."},{"time":457364,"text":"Now, having spent several months\ntrying everything I could think of to find"},{"time":461037,"text":"a book that had been translated\ninto English from the nation,"},{"time":464400,"text":"it seemed as though\nthe only option left to me"},{"time":466666,"text":"was to see if I could get something\ntranslated for me from scratch."},{"time":470404,"text":"Now, I was really dubious"},{"time":471929,"text":"whether anyone was going\nto want to help with this,"},{"time":474349,"text":"and give up their time\nfor something like that."},{"time":477525,"text":"But, within a week of me putting\na call out on Twitter and Facebook"},{"time":481812,"text":"for Portuguese speakers,"},{"time":483790,"text":"I had more people than I could\ninvolve in the project,"},{"time":487385,"text":"including Margaret Jull Costa,\na leader in her field,"},{"time":491767,"text":"who has translated the work\nof Nobel Prize winner José Saramago."},{"time":498443,"text":"With my nine volunteers in place,"},{"time":500402,"text":"I managed to find a book\nby a São Toméan author"},{"time":503014,"text":"that I could buy enough copies of online."},{"time":505548,"text":"Here's one of them."},{"time":507268,"text":"And I sent a copy out\nto each of my volunteers."},{"time":510856,"text":"They all took on a couple\nof short stories from this collection,"},{"time":514054,"text":"stuck to their word, sent\ntheir translations back to me,"},{"time":517705,"text":"and within six weeks,\nI had the entire book to read."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522422,"text":"In that case, as I found so often\nduring my year of reading the world,"},{"time":526908,"text":"my not knowing and being open\nabout my limitations"},{"time":531017,"text":"had become a big opportunity."},{"time":533935,"text":"When it came to São Tomé and Príncipe,"},{"time":536146,"text":"it was a chance not only\nto learn something new"},{"time":539516,"text":"and discover a new collection of stories,"},{"time":542215,"text":"but also to bring together\na group of people"},{"time":545185,"text":"and facilitate a joint creative endeavor."},{"time":548901,"text":"My weakness had become\nthe project's strength."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553929,"text":"The books I read that year\nopened my eyes to many things."},{"time":557509,"text":"As those who enjoy reading will know,"},{"time":559720,"text":"books have an extraordinary power\nto take you out of yourself"},{"time":563524,"text":"and into someone else's mindset,"},{"time":565692,"text":"so that, for a while at least,"},{"time":567558,"text":"you look at the world\nthrough different eyes."},{"time":570390,"text":"That can be an uncomfortable experience,"},{"time":572877,"text":"particularly if you're reading a book"},{"time":574673,"text":"from a culture that may have quite\ndifferent values to your own."},{"time":578601,"text":"But it can also be really enlightening."},{"time":581402,"text":"Wrestling with unfamiliar ideas\ncan help clarify your own thinking."},{"time":585742,"text":"And it can also show up blind spots"},{"time":587933,"text":"in the way you might have\nbeen looking at the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591072,"text":"When I looked back at much\nof the English-language literature"},{"time":593978,"text":"I'd grown up with, for example,"},{"time":595688,"text":"I began to see how narrow a lot of it was,"},{"time":598749,"text":"compared to the richness\nthat the world has to offer."},{"time":602886,"text":"And as the pages turned,"},{"time":605072,"text":"something else started to happen, too."},{"time":608150,"text":"Little by little,"},{"time":609325,"text":"that long list of countries that\nI'd started the year with, changed"},{"time":613634,"text":"from a rather dry, academic\nregister of place names"},{"time":618017,"text":"into living, breathing entities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621475,"text":"Now, I don't want to suggest\nthat it's at all possible"},{"time":624222,"text":"to get a rounded picture of a country\nsimply by reading one book."},{"time":629010,"text":"But cumulatively, the stories\nI read that year"},{"time":632623,"text":"made me more alive than ever before"},{"time":635707,"text":"to the richness, diversity and complexity\nof our remarkable planet."},{"time":642654,"text":"It was as though the world's stories"},{"time":644671,"text":"and the people who'd gone\nto such lengths to help me read them"},{"time":648595,"text":"had made it real to me."},{"time":652086,"text":"These days, when I look at my bookshelves"},{"time":654645,"text":"or consider the works on my e-reader,"},{"time":657794,"text":"they tell a rather different story."},{"time":660649,"text":"It's the story of the power\nbooks have to connect us"},{"time":664019,"text":"across political, geographical,\ncultural, social, religious divides."},{"time":669422,"text":"It's the tale of the potential\nhuman beings have to work together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":674320,"text":"And, it's testament"},{"time":675686,"text":"to the extraordinary times we live\nin, where, thanks to the Internet,"},{"time":680333,"text":"it's easier than ever before"},{"time":682274,"text":"for a stranger to share a story,\na worldview, a book"},{"time":686727,"text":"with someone she may never meet,\non the other side of the planet."},{"time":691595,"text":"I hope it's a story I'm reading\nfor many years to come."},{"time":695074,"text":"And I hope many more people will join me."},{"time":697947,"text":"If we all read more widely,\nthere'd be more incentive"},{"time":700585,"text":"for publishers to translate more books,"},{"time":703156,"text":"and we would all be richer for that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705713,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706894,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}